00:13:08.990 --> 00:13:10.990
There's more from where that came from

00:13:10.990 --> 00:13:11.990
once you give us a review.

00:13:11.990 --> 00:13:12.990
Give me a break.

00:13:12.990 --> 00:13:14.990
Tell Pat I don't accept free food,

00:13:14.990 --> 00:13:16.990
but he's welcome to buy an ad.

00:13:16.990 --> 00:13:24.020
Wait, thanks anyway.

00:13:24.020 --> 00:13:30.410
I know temptation is the root of bad bosses,

00:13:30.410 --> 00:13:32.410
but do they have to throw pizza with extra cheese

00:13:32.410 --> 00:13:34.410
and pepperoni into the equation?

00:13:34.410 --> 00:13:40.540
Those tough decisions keep getting tougher.

00:13:40.540 --> 00:13:44.540
Okay, I've read through Sam's review once, twice,

00:13:44.540 --> 00:13:48.540
three times you were out, and it's really, well, not good.

00:13:48.540 --> 00:13:50.540
It's not just the bad grammar,

00:13:50.540 --> 00:13:52.540
the incorrect punctuation, the awkward syntax.

00:13:52.540 --> 00:13:54.540
I mean, I guess I could correct all that,

00:13:54.540 --> 00:13:59.540
but it's riddled with cliches as the cliche goes.

00:13:59.540 --> 00:14:02.540
Now, here's a music review by one Leonard K. Adnoit.

00:14:02.540 --> 00:14:04.540
It's clear, it's sharp,

00:14:04.540 --> 00:14:07.540
and Lenny's the biggest, not to mention, most boring jerk around.

00:14:07.540 --> 00:14:09.540
I guess some people talk better than they write

00:14:09.540 --> 00:14:11.540
and some people write better than they talk.

00:14:11.540 --> 00:14:13.540
So I've gotta figure out a way to talk to Sam.

00:14:13.540 --> 00:14:15.540
I mean, what am I supposed to do?

00:14:15.540 --> 00:14:16.540
Why are my best friends?

00:14:16.540 --> 00:14:24.180
Sam, hi.

00:14:24.180 --> 00:14:26.180
Hi, Clarissa.

00:14:26.180 --> 00:14:27.180
So?

00:14:27.180 --> 00:14:29.180
So, buttons.

00:14:29.180 --> 00:14:31.180
So what'd you think?

00:14:31.180 --> 00:14:32.180
Think?

00:14:32.180 --> 00:14:33.180
Of my review.

00:14:33.180 --> 00:14:37.180
I really tried to capture the sound of the smashing pumpkins.

00:14:37.180 --> 00:14:39.180
Oh, yeah, I can tell.

00:14:39.180 --> 00:14:42.180
I want the reader to hear the music through my words.

00:14:42.180 --> 00:14:46.180
X-R-N-M-M-N-A-H.

00:14:46.180 --> 00:14:48.180
Is that a rumor?

00:14:48.180 --> 00:14:49.180
Cool, huh?

00:14:49.180 --> 00:14:51.180
I think that word really gives you a feel

00:14:51.180 --> 00:14:53.180
for the lyrics and the guitarist.

00:14:53.180 --> 00:14:55.180
Must've been rough on your computer spell check.

00:14:55.180 --> 00:14:58.180
So what'd you think about the lead?

00:14:58.180 --> 00:15:01.180
Uh, the sound of silence cannot compare

00:15:01.180 --> 00:15:03.180
to the sound of the smashing pumpkins,

00:15:03.180 --> 00:15:05.180
which is anything but silent.

00:15:05.180 --> 00:15:07.180
In fact, it's not silent at all.

00:15:07.180 --> 00:15:09.180
It's loud, and I turned it way up

00:15:09.180 --> 00:15:11.180
to bring this review to you fellow listeners,

00:15:11.180 --> 00:15:13.180
or in this case, readers.

00:15:13.180 --> 00:15:15.180
Does it grab you?

00:15:15.180 --> 00:15:16.180
Definitely grabs something.

00:15:16.180 --> 00:15:17.180
Thanks, Clarissa.

00:15:17.180 --> 00:15:19.180
I knew I wouldn't let you down.

00:15:19.180 --> 00:15:20.180
I gotta go tell my daddy

00:15:20.180 --> 00:15:22.180
he's not the only newsman in the family.

00:15:22.180 --> 00:15:24.180
I'm really glad you like it.

00:15:24.180 --> 00:15:26.180
Hold it. Did I say like?

00:15:26.180 --> 00:15:28.180
I don't think I said like.

00:15:28.180 --> 00:15:30.180
You mean you don't like it?

00:15:30.180 --> 00:15:31.180
Well...

00:15:31.180 --> 00:15:33.180
Well, what?

00:15:33.180 --> 00:15:35.180
It's... Well, it's...

00:15:35.180 --> 00:15:36.180
You think it stinks.

00:15:36.180 --> 00:15:38.180
I wouldn't say stinks, exactly.

00:15:38.180 --> 00:15:40.180
Well, you might as well have.

00:15:40.180 --> 00:15:42.180
Well, we'll have to work on it, Sam.

00:15:42.180 --> 00:15:43.180
Thanks a lot.

00:15:43.180 --> 00:15:45.180
I poured my heart and soul into that review.

00:15:45.180 --> 00:15:47.180
Maybe it's not perfect.

00:15:47.180 --> 00:15:49.180
Maybe I made up a few words.

00:15:49.180 --> 00:15:50.180
Misspelled a few.

00:15:50.180 --> 00:15:52.180
Who said I was a great speller?

00:15:52.180 --> 00:15:54.180
Incomplete sentences, poor syntax.

00:15:54.180 --> 00:15:56.180
Okay, okay. Let's just forget it.

00:15:56.180 --> 00:15:58.180
Well, Sam, I thought we could work on it.

00:15:58.180 --> 00:16:03.060
Great.

00:16:03.060 --> 00:16:04.060
The quickest way to lose your friends

00:16:04.060 --> 00:16:06.060
is to become their editor.

00:16:06.060 --> 00:16:20.180
And it started off so well.

00:16:20.180 --> 00:16:22.180
A cub reporter soon catapulted her

00:16:22.180 --> 00:16:25.180
to the role of Empress of Newsprint.

00:16:25.180 --> 00:16:31.220
Defeat.

00:16:31.220 --> 00:16:33.220
Unable to meet the constant demands

00:16:33.220 --> 00:16:35.220
that she employed,

00:16:35.220 --> 00:16:37.220
Darling soon lost her grasp

00:16:37.220 --> 00:16:44.400
on all for which she had once cared.

00:16:44.400 --> 00:16:46.400
Never photographed.

00:16:46.400 --> 00:16:48.400
The once great editor paid a price.

00:16:48.400 --> 00:16:49.400
Cost?

00:16:49.400 --> 00:17:00.620
No man can say.

00:17:00.620 --> 00:17:02.620
Oh, stop the presses.

00:17:02.620 --> 00:17:04.620
I'd better revise the situation fast

00:17:04.620 --> 00:17:06.620
before it all goes up in smoke.

00:17:06.620 --> 00:17:14.060
More Clarissa.

00:17:14.060 --> 00:17:17.060
More Snake. After this.

