Part of this complete breakfast.

00:18:57.280 --> 00:19:00.280
The creators of Squiggle Wiggle Writer and Squiggle Ball.

00:19:00.280 --> 00:19:07.440
Watching Clarissa Explains It All.

00:19:07.440 --> 00:19:19.840
I've been up since five this morning

00:19:19.840 --> 00:19:22.840
trying to fit in all the news that's unfit to print.

00:19:22.840 --> 00:19:23.840
I really want to be fair.

00:19:23.840 --> 00:19:25.840
I really want to make this issue great

00:19:25.840 --> 00:19:27.840
and I wouldn't mind making everyone happy,

00:19:27.840 --> 00:19:29.840
but I guess something's got to give.

00:19:29.840 --> 00:19:30.840
First, there's Dad.

00:19:30.840 --> 00:19:32.840
It's nice that he wants to help,

00:19:32.840 --> 00:19:35.840
but he keeps giving me ideas I can't use.

00:19:35.840 --> 00:19:37.840
I just don't think the Thomas Tupper Times

00:19:37.840 --> 00:19:41.840
is ready for a 3D glow-in-the-dark scratch-and-sniff logo.

00:19:41.840 --> 00:19:43.840
On the other hand,

00:19:43.840 --> 00:19:46.840
is anyone ready for Ferguson the filmmaker?

00:19:46.840 --> 00:19:49.840
He's turned the bathroom into his private special effects studio.

00:19:49.840 --> 00:19:52.840
I guess even George Lucas had to start somewhere.

00:19:52.840 --> 00:19:55.840
And I've spent hours trying to turn Sam's review

00:19:55.840 --> 00:19:57.840
into something the paper can print.

00:19:57.840 --> 00:19:59.840
But after I got through editing it,

00:19:59.840 --> 00:20:03.090
there was only one word left.

00:20:03.090 --> 00:20:06.090
And I finally decided on my subject for my editorial.

00:20:06.090 --> 00:20:07.090
Teen Runaways.

00:20:07.090 --> 00:20:09.090
Now, if only I could find some time to write it.

00:20:09.090 --> 00:20:12.090
Too bad I can't give myself an extension on that deadline.

00:20:12.090 --> 00:20:15.090
Um, I noticed that in all of your films,

00:20:15.090 --> 00:20:19.090
Angora's Swerters and Kulot's figured very prominently.

00:20:19.090 --> 00:20:21.090
That's very astute.

00:20:21.090 --> 00:20:22.090
Ah, thank you.

00:20:22.090 --> 00:20:25.090
Um, well, could you elaborate on the Kulot motif?

00:20:25.090 --> 00:20:29.090
I prefer to leave the deeper meaning ambiguous.

00:20:29.090 --> 00:20:33.090
Ah, wise.

00:20:33.090 --> 00:20:37.810
A whole new batch of catalogs.

00:20:37.810 --> 00:20:41.600
Hey, look at this.

00:20:41.600 --> 00:20:44.600
A self-inverting aerobics machine.

00:20:44.600 --> 00:20:48.600
Experience the healthy benefits of hanging it upside down.

00:20:48.600 --> 00:20:50.600
How could we get off these manless...

00:20:50.600 --> 00:20:52.600
Think of those poor trees.

00:20:52.600 --> 00:20:55.600
Ah, well, then you will love this home paper recycling milk.

00:20:55.600 --> 00:20:58.600
Oh, that's brilliant.

00:20:59.600 --> 00:21:00.600
Who are you?

00:21:00.600 --> 00:21:04.600
Dad, this is Turner B. Gerhard.

00:21:04.600 --> 00:21:06.600
I'm sure you've heard of him.

00:21:06.600 --> 00:21:07.600
No.

00:21:07.600 --> 00:21:11.600
Well, no doubt you're familiar with my ove.

00:21:11.600 --> 00:21:14.600
What ove is that?

00:21:14.600 --> 00:21:17.600
His films are classics, Dad.

00:21:17.600 --> 00:21:19.600
I'm writing the definitive interview.

00:21:19.600 --> 00:21:21.600
Bloody brilliant boy, Ferguson.

00:21:21.600 --> 00:21:24.600
To think he comes from such hearty, simple studs.

00:21:24.600 --> 00:21:26.600
Well, it was nice to meet you, Mr. Gerhard.

00:21:26.600 --> 00:21:31.600
Well, let's see if we can find a place for that recycler out back.

00:21:31.600 --> 00:21:34.600
Your parents are so... to real.

00:21:34.600 --> 00:21:36.600
Hmm, thank you.

00:21:36.600 --> 00:21:37.600
Aren't they, though?

00:21:37.600 --> 00:21:39.600
We're very big on reality here.

00:21:39.600 --> 00:21:41.600
Hello, Chief.

00:21:41.600 --> 00:21:44.600
My subject and I were just doing a little bit of fine-tuning on the in-depth profile.

00:21:44.600 --> 00:21:46.600
It's brilliant. Bloody brilliant.

00:21:46.600 --> 00:21:48.600
Your brother is just...

00:21:48.600 --> 00:21:50.600
Well, he's bloody brilliant, that's all.

00:21:50.600 --> 00:21:52.600
Ferguson showed you the piece?

00:21:52.600 --> 00:21:58.600
Finally, a film scholar who grasped the importance of my breakthrough film with Chef Wally.

00:21:58.600 --> 00:22:01.600
Well, TBG, let's get back to work.

00:22:01.600 --> 00:22:05.600
Yes, we just need to, uh, punch up these quotes on pur.

00:22:05.600 --> 00:22:08.600
Ferguson, can I talk to you in moment?

00:22:08.600 --> 00:22:10.600
Absolument, chief.

00:22:10.600 --> 00:22:14.600
You see, TBG, I know un pur des Français.

00:22:14.600 --> 00:22:19.290
Bloody trivia.

00:22:19.290 --> 00:22:21.290
Ferguson, what is he doing here?

00:22:21.290 --> 00:22:24.290
He just wanted to look over the interview before it went to press.

00:22:24.290 --> 00:22:26.290
He's completely unethical.

00:22:26.290 --> 00:22:30.290
You don't show your subject an article before it's published, especially a review.

00:22:30.290 --> 00:22:32.290
But he's made some really good revisions.

00:22:32.290 --> 00:22:35.290
Besides, he's not just my subject, he's...

00:22:35.290 --> 00:22:37.290
What, Ferguson?

00:22:37.290 --> 00:22:41.290
Well, you know, I'm writing a little PR for him while he's in town.

00:22:41.290 --> 00:22:45.290
What? Do the words journalistic integrity mean anything to you?

00:22:45.290 --> 00:22:48.290
I'm just doing it as a favor.

00:22:48.290 --> 00:22:50.290
Gerhard's agreed to introduce me to Hollywood.

00:22:50.290 --> 00:22:53.290
He thinks my reel is brilliant. Bloody brilliant.

00:22:53.290 --> 00:22:55.290
What's the only thing that'll be bloody if you don't get rid of him?

00:22:55.290 --> 00:22:56.290
Sis.

00:22:56.290 --> 00:22:59.080
Now.

00:22:59.080 --> 00:23:01.080
Whatever you say, chief.

00:23:01.080 --> 00:23:05.080
I was just having an petite conference with my editor.

00:23:05.080 --> 00:23:09.080
Fergie, she's... she's quite lovely, your sister.

00:23:09.080 --> 00:23:12.080
My mind is racing.

00:23:14.080 --> 00:23:16.080
Beautiful young editor.

00:23:16.080 --> 00:23:22.080
Battles giant alien insect while wearing angora collars.

00:23:22.080 --> 00:23:23.080
What do you think?

00:23:23.080 --> 00:23:26.080
Brain dead. Bloody brain dead.

00:23:28.080 --> 00:23:41.860
Does anybody live here but me?

00:23:41.860 --> 00:23:48.210
Our pizza is good.

00:23:48.210 --> 00:23:50.210
And you really should. Try it.

00:23:50.210 --> 00:23:52.210
In fact, it's great.

00:23:52.210 --> 00:23:55.210
So go ahead and write about what you ate.

00:23:55.210 --> 00:23:57.210
Not again.

00:23:57.210 --> 00:23:59.210
Look, I already told Pats I can't accept freebies.

00:23:59.210 --> 00:24:02.210
Pats, I'm from Peppies.

00:24:02.210 --> 00:24:06.210
Well, tell Peppie he's welcome to put the poem in an ad.

00:24:07.210 --> 00:24:13.460
Wait. Thanks, that should do it.

00:24:13.460 --> 00:24:19.500
Hey, it's Hillary Rodham Clinton.

00:24:19.500 --> 00:24:21.500
Can send back all those free designer dresses?

00:24:21.500 --> 00:24:24.500
I guess I can live with giving up a few free pizzas.

00:24:24.500 --> 00:24:29.100
A thousand thanks, maestro.

00:24:29.100 --> 00:24:34.100
It's bloody fantastic working with a true cinematic genius.

00:24:34.100 --> 00:24:37.100
Ferg, my son, it's a bloody brilliant screenplay.

00:24:37.100 --> 00:24:39.100
And with that brilliant special effects reel of yours,

00:24:39.100 --> 00:24:44.100
I can see no reason why you can't co-direct it under my wing.

00:24:44.100 --> 00:24:47.100
What screenplay, Ferguson?

00:24:47.100 --> 00:24:49.100
The cockroach that ate New York for breakfast?

00:24:49.100 --> 00:24:52.100
Just a little something I've been working up on this side.

00:24:52.100 --> 00:24:54.100
I already see the sequel.

00:24:54.100 --> 00:24:57.100
The water bug that ate L.A. for lunch.

00:24:57.100 --> 00:25:00.100
Don't they do lunch in L.A.?

00:25:00.100 --> 00:25:02.100
Oh, yes.

00:25:02.100 --> 00:25:04.100
That's very funny, Ferguson.

00:25:04.100 --> 00:25:06.100
Bloody funny.

00:25:06.100 --> 00:25:08.100
So long, my brilliant aficionado.

00:25:08.100 --> 00:25:11.100
You will be at my Meet the Fans video signing, won't you?

00:25:11.100 --> 00:25:14.100
How could your biggest fan miss it?

00:25:14.100 --> 00:25:16.100
Biggest fool is more like it.

00:25:16.100 --> 00:25:18.100
Don't be jealous, sis.

00:25:18.100 --> 00:25:20.100
I'll give you a cameo.

00:25:20.100 --> 00:25:22.100
You could be the giant cockroach's first victim.

00:25:22.100 --> 00:25:24.100
Ferguson, I can't publish your article.

00:25:24.100 --> 00:25:27.100
You have to write a genuine interview, not a puff piece.

00:25:27.100 --> 00:25:29.100
Then I'll save it for my book.

00:25:29.100 --> 00:25:31.100
Turner B. Gerhard, The Authorized Bio.

00:25:31.100 --> 00:25:34.100
You can't just cop out on me. I've allotted space for it.

00:25:34.100 --> 00:25:37.100
Sorry, sis. Hollywood calls.

00:25:37.100 --> 00:25:41.100
I think I'll have a spot of tea while working on my shooting draft.

00:25:43.100 --> 00:25:46.100
Oh, by the way, good luck with your little journalism project.

00:25:46.100 --> 00:25:51.140
I'd love to flatten Ferguson to the ground.

00:25:51.140 --> 00:25:53.140
I know you can't run away from your problems,

00:25:53.140 --> 00:25:56.140
but why can't you run over them with a 10-ton truck?

00:25:56.140 --> 00:26:04.100
So I guess it's time for the Thomas Tupper Times to be put to bed,

00:26:04.100 --> 00:26:06.100
and I don't mean under the covers.

00:26:06.100 --> 00:26:08.100
I mean, the paper is ready to go to press.

00:26:08.100 --> 00:26:10.100
Almost.

00:26:10.100 --> 00:26:12.100
First, I thought I'd take a shot at reworking Sam's review.

00:26:12.100 --> 00:26:15.100
The bad news? It's not a pretty picture.

00:26:15.100 --> 00:26:17.100
But there's good news.

00:26:17.100 --> 00:26:19.100
It turns out the back of Sam's review?

00:26:19.100 --> 00:26:21.100
It's worth a thousand words.

00:26:21.100 --> 00:26:23.100
It'll be the first cartoon you've ever run.

00:26:23.100 --> 00:26:26.420
Hi, Sam.

00:26:26.420 --> 00:26:31.900
Hey, Clarissa.

00:26:31.900 --> 00:26:33.900
Thanks for coming over.

00:26:33.900 --> 00:26:35.900
No problem. I'm glad you called.

00:26:35.900 --> 00:26:38.900
Listen, about the review, I'm sorry I overreacted.

00:26:38.900 --> 00:26:40.900
I understand, Sam. You were tired in that review,

00:26:40.900 --> 00:26:42.900
and I should have been more clear.

00:26:42.900 --> 00:26:44.900
Oh, I got the message.

00:26:44.900 --> 00:26:46.900
I mean more specific.

00:26:46.900 --> 00:26:48.900
I was really planning to help you rewrite it.

00:26:48.900 --> 00:26:50.900
That's okay. You don't need to.

00:26:50.900 --> 00:26:52.900
I've got something all finished, ready to print.

00:26:52.900 --> 00:26:54.900
You wrote another review?

00:26:54.900 --> 00:26:56.900
No, it's the one I took back.

00:26:56.900 --> 00:26:58.900
