as stick continues.

00:45:21.820 --> 00:45:23.820
Honest Abe Lincoln once said

00:45:23.820 --> 00:45:25.820
a house divided against itself

00:45:25.820 --> 00:45:27.820
cannot stand.

00:45:29.820 --> 00:45:31.820
I'll bet his dad was a bowler too.

00:45:31.820 --> 00:45:33.820
It's hard to believe that our friendship

00:45:33.820 --> 00:45:35.820
was ending over a piece of molten rock.

00:45:35.820 --> 00:45:37.820
But the battle lines were drawn.

00:45:37.820 --> 00:45:39.820
Pete took his half of the bunk

00:45:39.820 --> 00:45:41.820
and moved to the basement.

00:45:41.820 --> 00:45:43.820
We were no longer talking.

00:45:43.820 --> 00:45:45.820
Any messages we had, we sent

00:45:45.820 --> 00:45:54.730
through Ellen.

00:45:54.730 --> 00:45:56.730
We even had a system so we didn't have to

00:45:56.730 --> 00:46:08.100
see each other at meals.

00:46:08.100 --> 00:46:10.100
Don, you have got to put

00:46:10.100 --> 00:46:12.100
a stop to this.

00:46:12.100 --> 00:46:14.100
It's gone too far.

00:46:14.100 --> 00:46:16.100
Maybe she's right, Dad.

00:46:16.100 --> 00:46:18.100
Maybe she is.

00:46:18.100 --> 00:46:20.100
And maybe she isn't.

00:46:20.100 --> 00:46:22.100
Even with Artie guarding the house

00:46:22.100 --> 00:46:24.100
the whole thing felt out of control.

00:46:24.100 --> 00:46:26.100
Careful boy, careful!

00:46:26.100 --> 00:46:28.100
There are unfavorable

00:46:28.100 --> 00:46:30.100
omens in the air.

00:46:30.100 --> 00:46:32.100
You finished painting your dad's room yet?

00:46:32.100 --> 00:46:39.740
I couldn't.

00:46:39.740 --> 00:46:41.740
Pete wallpaper did last night

00:46:41.740 --> 00:46:43.740
and put down carpet.

00:46:43.740 --> 00:46:45.740
Ellen, this is insane.

00:46:45.740 --> 00:46:47.740
We even talked in

00:46:47.740 --> 00:46:49.740
in two weeks.

00:46:49.740 --> 00:46:51.740
We've never gone that long without talking.

00:46:51.740 --> 00:46:55.940
War is ugly, Pete.

00:46:55.940 --> 00:46:57.940
But he's my best friend.

00:46:57.940 --> 00:46:59.940
I feel funny saying this,

00:46:59.940 --> 00:47:01.940
but maybe your best friendship

00:47:01.940 --> 00:47:03.940
wasn't meant to last forever.

00:47:03.940 --> 00:47:05.940
Friends do grow apart sometimes

00:47:05.940 --> 00:47:07.940
and you are four years older.

00:47:07.940 --> 00:47:11.290
Think about it.

00:47:11.290 --> 00:47:13.290
Your brothers.

00:47:13.290 --> 00:47:16.700
How many brothers do you know who are best friends?

00:47:16.700 --> 00:47:20.650
And so the war

00:47:20.650 --> 00:47:22.650
raged on.

00:47:22.650 --> 00:47:24.650
My brother, one of the greatest

00:47:24.650 --> 00:47:26.650
natural generals ever born,

00:47:26.650 --> 00:47:30.150
began a full frontal assault.

00:47:30.150 --> 00:47:32.150
Pete says he's responsible,

00:47:32.150 --> 00:47:34.150
but last year he broke the whole vase.

00:47:34.150 --> 00:47:36.150
Pete says he loves his parents,

00:47:36.150 --> 00:47:38.150
but he didn't buy their anniversary card.

00:47:38.150 --> 00:47:40.150
He just signed it and for the algebra final

00:47:40.150 --> 00:47:42.150
Pete had to borrow notes.

00:47:42.150 --> 00:47:44.150
Broke the vase, signed the card,

00:47:44.150 --> 00:47:46.150
borrowed notes.

00:47:46.150 --> 00:47:48.150
You need someone you can trust

00:47:48.150 --> 00:47:50.150
with your bowling ball.

00:47:50.150 --> 00:47:52.150
Give it to Pete. He deserves it.

00:47:52.150 --> 00:47:54.150
Pay for by the committee to give Pete the bowling ball.

00:47:54.150 --> 00:47:56.150
If I was going to win

00:47:56.150 --> 00:47:58.150
I'd have to beat him at his own game.

00:47:58.150 --> 00:48:00.150
Issue one.

00:48:00.150 --> 00:48:02.150
Dad's bowling ball.

00:48:02.150 --> 00:48:04.150
Who deserves the celebrated sphere?

00:48:04.150 --> 00:48:06.150
Item.

00:48:06.150 --> 00:48:08.150
Young Pete toppled the Asian Bond Market.

00:48:08.150 --> 00:48:10.150
Item. Young Pete's science project

00:48:10.150 --> 00:48:12.150
caused spontaneous baldness

00:48:12.150 --> 00:48:14.150
across the Texas Panhandle.

00:48:14.150 --> 00:48:16.150
Item. Young Pete accidentally

00:48:16.150 --> 00:48:18.150
drained Lake Superior.

00:48:18.150 --> 00:48:20.150
His response?

00:48:20.150 --> 00:48:22.150
No comment, Grunge Bag!

00:48:22.150 --> 00:48:24.150
No comment, Grunge Bag?

00:48:24.150 --> 00:48:26.150
Not good enough.

00:48:26.150 --> 00:48:28.150
Exit question. Who gets the ball?

00:48:28.150 --> 00:48:30.150
Young Pete? Wrong.

00:48:30.150 --> 00:48:32.150
Answer. Older Pete.

00:48:32.150 --> 00:48:34.150
Bye-bye.

00:48:34.150 --> 00:48:36.150
Mom had had enough.

00:48:36.150 --> 00:48:38.150
She wasn't going to let our family

00:48:38.150 --> 00:48:40.150
fall apart over a bowling ball.

00:48:46.150 --> 00:48:52.890
Honey, something wrong?

00:48:54.890 --> 00:48:56.890
See, my mom had a metal plate in her head

00:48:56.890 --> 00:48:58.890
from an accident she had when she was a kid

00:48:58.890 --> 00:49:00.890
and they both knew it would attract

00:49:00.890 --> 00:49:02.890
every lightning bolt for miles.

00:49:02.890 --> 00:49:04.890
Come inside, right now!

00:49:06.890 --> 00:49:08.890
Not until you stop this war.

00:49:10.890 --> 00:49:12.890
I can't.

00:49:12.890 --> 00:49:14.890
He will read me.

00:49:14.890 --> 00:49:16.890
If you don't stand up to your father

00:49:16.890 --> 00:49:18.890
I'm going to blow myself

00:49:18.890 --> 00:49:20.890
to kingdom come.

00:49:20.890 --> 00:49:22.890
Dad had no choice.

00:49:22.890 --> 00:49:24.890
Maybe he didn't have the guts to face his dad

00:49:24.890 --> 00:49:26.890
but he got another idea.

00:49:26.890 --> 00:49:31.450
Later that night

00:49:31.450 --> 00:49:33.450
he snuck rolling thunder from the house

00:49:35.450 --> 00:49:37.450
and ran four hours

00:49:37.450 --> 00:49:39.450
to the Canadian Borger.

00:49:39.450 --> 00:49:48.620
Go on, what are you waiting for?

00:49:48.620 --> 00:49:50.620
You're free.

00:49:50.620 --> 00:49:55.270
You took it!

00:49:55.270 --> 00:50:11.320
Maybe it was stolen.

00:50:11.320 --> 00:50:14.860
I thought I heard a noise last night.

00:50:14.860 --> 00:50:16.860
Spunky.

00:50:16.860 --> 00:50:18.860
Have you done something?

00:50:18.860 --> 00:50:20.860
No.

00:50:20.860 --> 00:50:22.860
I know.

00:50:22.860 --> 00:50:24.860
I know that looks

00:50:24.860 --> 00:50:26.860
you've done something.

00:50:26.860 --> 00:50:28.860
Tell Papa.

00:50:28.860 --> 00:50:30.860
What difference does it make?

00:50:30.860 --> 00:50:32.860
It's gone!

00:50:32.860 --> 00:50:34.860
Now we can get back to normal.

00:50:36.860 --> 00:50:38.860
But we all knew

00:50:38.860 --> 00:50:40.860
things would never be normal again

00:50:40.860 --> 00:50:42.860
and that's when we heard it.

00:50:46.970 --> 00:50:48.970
Rolling thunder!

00:50:53.370 --> 00:50:55.370
No one knew how it got back

00:50:55.370 --> 00:50:57.370
but one thing was certain

00:50:57.370 --> 00:50:59.370
we had to settle this thing

00:50:59.370 --> 00:51:01.370
once and for all.

00:51:03.370 --> 00:51:05.370
Sometimes the only way to stop a war

00:51:05.370 --> 00:51:07.370
is to fight the bloodiest battle ever.

00:51:07.370 --> 00:51:09.370
A battle so gruesome

00:51:09.370 --> 00:51:11.370
there can only be one undisputed winner.

00:51:11.370 --> 00:51:13.370
Me and Pete were going to stare.

00:51:13.370 --> 00:51:15.370
And one and two.

00:51:15.370 --> 00:51:17.370
And one and two.

00:51:17.370 --> 00:51:19.370
Not only were the stakes

00:51:19.370 --> 00:51:21.370
higher than any other staring contest

00:51:21.370 --> 00:51:23.370
but the only way

00:51:23.370 --> 00:51:25.370
to lose was to smile

00:51:25.370 --> 00:51:27.370
and neither of us

00:51:27.370 --> 00:51:29.370
felt like smiling.

00:51:29.370 --> 00:51:31.370
Must destroy.

00:51:31.370 --> 00:51:33.370
Must destroy.

00:51:33.370 --> 00:51:35.370
Pete!

00:51:35.370 --> 00:51:37.370
Artie understood the contest

00:51:37.370 --> 00:51:39.370
could go on for weeks, even years

00:51:39.370 --> 00:51:41.370
so he decided to come

00:51:41.370 --> 00:51:43.370
to our rescue.

00:51:43.370 --> 00:51:45.370
You know what I've come for,

00:51:45.370 --> 00:51:47.370
grand puppy?

00:51:47.370 --> 00:51:51.380
The ball!

00:51:51.380 --> 00:51:53.380
Out with it, old man!

00:51:53.380 --> 00:51:55.380
You'll be sorry.

00:52:03.210 --> 00:52:05.210
Disrupt our families!

00:52:05.210 --> 00:52:07.210
Get her lover!

00:52:07.210 --> 00:52:11.830
Blue Legless Dog!

00:52:11.830 --> 00:52:33.100
This!

00:52:33.100 --> 00:52:35.100
The battle went on for hours.

00:52:35.100 --> 00:52:37.100
The ball was the fiercest

00:52:37.100 --> 00:52:39.100
faux Artie had ever tangled with.

00:52:39.100 --> 00:52:42.790
And in the end

00:52:42.790 --> 00:52:44.790
the strong man went down.

00:52:44.790 --> 00:52:48.100
Foolish man.

00:52:48.100 --> 00:52:50.100
Brave.

00:52:50.100 --> 00:52:52.100
But foolish.

00:52:52.100 --> 00:53:01.940
With Artie defeated

00:53:01.940 --> 00:53:03.940
nothing could stop us

00:53:03.940 --> 00:53:05.940
from the madness of the final showdown.

00:53:05.940 --> 00:53:07.940
Two Pete's

00:53:07.940 --> 00:53:09.940
would enter that room.

00:53:09.940 --> 00:53:11.940
Only one

00:53:11.940 --> 00:53:13.940
would come out.

00:53:13.940 --> 00:53:15.940
It's not too late to stop.

00:53:15.940 --> 00:53:17.940
Quit stalling, Chunderhead!

00:53:17.940 --> 00:53:19.940
Make me laugh!

00:53:19.940 --> 00:53:21.940
And so it began.

00:53:21.940 --> 00:53:23.940
At first

00:53:23.940 --> 00:53:25.940
we just stood there probing

00:53:25.940 --> 00:53:27.940
each other for weaknesses.

00:53:27.940 --> 00:53:29.940
Then suddenly

00:53:29.940 --> 00:53:33.900
Pete attacked with a barrage

00:53:33.900 --> 00:53:35.900
of face twitches and tongue swirls

00:53:35.900 --> 00:53:37.900
that normally would have obliterated me.

00:53:37.900 --> 00:53:39.900
But I was ready

00:53:39.900 --> 00:53:41.900
and came right back

00:53:41.900 --> 00:53:43.900
with the Wisconsin ear wiggle I picked up

00:53:43.900 --> 00:53:45.900
last summer in Sheboygan.

00:53:45.900 --> 00:53:47.900
I caught him off guard,

00:53:47.900 --> 00:53:49.900
but he didn't crack a smile.

00:53:49.900 --> 00:54:09.560
The battle was raging.

00:54:09.560 --> 00:54:11.560
Meanwhile

00:54:11.560 --> 00:54:13.560
my dad was fighting his own battle.

00:54:13.560 --> 00:54:15.560
It started when Grandpa brought out

00:54:15.560 --> 00:54:19.740
cookies and milk.

00:54:19.740 --> 00:54:21.740
Maybe we should go up there.

00:54:21.740 --> 00:54:23.740
No, I forbid it.

00:54:23.740 --> 00:54:25.740
The ball must be passed on.

00:54:25.740 --> 00:54:27.740
Nothing can stop it.

00:54:27.740 --> 00:54:31.370
Drink that.

00:54:31.370 --> 00:54:37.880
It's milk.

00:54:37.880 --> 00:54:39.880
The contest slogged on

00:54:39.880 --> 00:54:41.880
for hour after brutal hour.

00:54:41.880 --> 00:54:43.880
The way it was going,

00:54:43.880 --> 00:54:45.880
maybe it would last the rest of our lives.

00:54:45.880 --> 00:54:47.880
It was insane.

00:54:47.880 --> 00:54:49.880
It was inhuman.

00:54:49.880 --> 00:54:51.880
Without warning, both of us

00:54:51.880 --> 00:55:03.100
had

00:55:03.100 --> 00:55:05.100
faced off against each other.

00:55:05.100 --> 00:55:07.100
Dad finally got up the nerve

00:55:07.100 --> 00:55:09.100
to face off against his dad.

00:55:11.100 --> 00:55:13.100
Who ate all the cookies?

00:55:13.100 --> 00:55:15.100
You know what sugar does to your teeth?

00:55:15.100 --> 00:55:17.100
Come on out with it.

00:55:17.100 --> 00:55:19.100
Who did it?

00:55:19.100 --> 00:55:21.100
You want to know who ate the cookies?

00:55:21.100 --> 00:55:23.100
You want to know? I'll tell you.

00:55:23.100 --> 00:55:25.100
I ate the cookies. And you want to know what else?

00:55:25.100 --> 00:55:27.100
I didn't finish my milk.

00:55:27.100 --> 00:55:29.100
What do you think of that?

00:55:29.100 --> 00:55:32.570
My name is not Spunky.

00:55:32.570 --> 00:55:34.570
My name is

00:55:34.570 --> 00:55:36.570
Dad.

00:55:36.570 --> 00:55:38.570
This is my house and my wife

00:55:38.570 --> 00:55:40.570
and my kids. And that ball

00:55:40.570 --> 00:55:42.570
is out of here. This war

00:55:42.570 --> 00:55:44.570
is over.

00:55:44.570 --> 00:55:46.570
But it wasn't.

00:55:46.570 --> 00:55:48.570
Me and Pete were locked in a death stare

00:55:48.570 --> 00:55:50.570
that nothing could break.

00:55:50.570 --> 00:55:52.570
As the intensity increased,

00:55:52.570 --> 00:55:54.570
I started to hallucinate.

00:55:54.570 --> 00:56:06.620
And I know he was

00:56:06.620 --> 00:56:08.620
going through the same thing.

00:56:08.620 --> 00:56:10.620
Pete! Pete!

00:56:10.620 --> 00:56:12.620
Open the door!

00:56:12.620 --> 00:56:14.620
I didn't know how much longer we could take it.

00:56:14.620 --> 00:56:16.620
But then

00:56:16.620 --> 00:56:18.620
something happened.

00:56:18.620 --> 00:56:20.620
I was able to see Pete again

